      "lineNbr": 114,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-02T01:08:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Check Context.Done at the beginning of each loop, in order to stop if the Context is cancelled.\n\nselect {\ncase \u003c-c.Done():\n  ch \u003c- logResp{nil, c.Err()}:\n  return\ndefault:\n}\n\nAlternatively, since I\u0027m not 100% sure that the consumer will always be running at this point, you may want to have a separate \"overall\" buffered error channel that you can write to, to stop goroutines from blocking forever if their consumer loops have terminated.\n\nYou can do this by:\n1) Making \"fetch\" return an error.\n2) Having \"startFetch\" return a \"chan error\", with buffer size 1.\n3) Changing \"go fetch(...)\" to: \"go func() { errC \u003c- fetch(...) }\"\n4) Having consumer consume this value at the end of its loop, for an overall fetch status.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 114,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 114,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "bf42f9cea0719e9379bf600750847fd342f9b06f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
